org.archive.wayback.partition

Class BubbleCalendarData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.archive.wayback.partition.BubbleCalendarData

  • public class BubbleCalendarData
extends Object
    Support bean for rendering capture calendar.

    Despite name, this class is generally useful for different calendar styles.

    Initialize with UIResults that is set up with CaptureSearchResults and WaybackRequest.

    Caveat: Although fields are all public for historical reasons, please use getters for reading their values. Field access-level will be changed in the future.

    Author:
    brad

      • getCaptureCalendar

        public List<List<Partition<CaptureSearchResult>>> getCaptureCalendar()
        return CaptureSearchResult partitions for the month grouped by week. Call this method after designating desired month with setMonth(int). Each week group has exactly seven elements, where out-of-month slots are null.
        Returns:
        Weekly list of Partitions
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if month is not in 0..11 range.
